---
import { recommendedNewsletters, recommendedCreators } from '../data/site';
import Button from './Button.astro';
import Icon from './Icon.astro';
---

<section class="bg-neutral-lightest py-16 md:py-24 px-4 md:px-10 bg-pattern-dots">
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
    <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl md:text-3xl font-semibold title-bar mb-2">
      Let's not stop the fullstack love
    </h2>
    <p class="text-base md:text-lg text-neutral-medium mb-6 max-w-[700px]">
      Always keep learning and staying inspired.
    </p>
    <p class="text-base md:text-lg text-neutral-dark mb-6 max-w-[700px] leading-relaxed">
      There's no replacing FullStack Bulletin. It was unique in its own way. But that doesn't mean the
      world isn't still full of beautiful places and people that you can learn from and be inspired by.
    </p>
    <p class="text-base md:text-lg text-neutral-dark mb-12 max-w-[700px] leading-relaxed">
      Many of these are the same resources from which we drew inspiration for our newsletter
      and often a direct source of the content we proposed every week. They are all worth your time.
    </p>

    <div class="mb-12">
      <h3 class="font-heading text-lg font-semibold mb-6">Newsletters and websites</h3>
      <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
        {recommendedNewsletters.map((resource) => (
          <a
            href={resource.url}
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
            class="inline-flex items-center px-4 py-2 bg-white border border-neutral-light/50 rounded-full text-sm font-heading text-neutral-darkest hover:border-brand-primary hover:bg-brand-primary/15 hover:shadow-sm transition-all duration-200"
          >
            {resource.name}
          </a>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="mb-12">
      <h3 class="font-heading text-lg font-semibold mb-6">Amazing creators and builders to follow</h3>
      <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
        {recommendedCreators.map((creator) => (
          <a
            href={creator.url}
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
            class="inline-flex items-center px-4 py-2 bg-white border border-neutral-light/50 rounded-full text-sm font-heading text-neutral-darkest hover:border-brand-primary hover:bg-brand-primary/15 hover:shadow-sm transition-all duration-200"
          >
            {creator.name}
          </a>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="border border-brand-primary/30 bg-brand-primary/5 rounded-lg p-6 max-w-[700px]">
      <p class="text-base text-neutral-dark leading-relaxed mb-4">
        Want to follow all of them in one go? Here's an OPML file you can import into your favourite RSS reader for a unified stream of fullstack inspiration.
      </p>
      <Button href="/fullstackbulletin-recommended-feeds.opml" variant="primary" size="md" download>
        <Icon name="rss" size={16} />
        Download OPML
      </Button>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
